{"kind": "text", "text": "] and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lahumo A^ayodK qiSaArN", "text_ar": "لَهُمْ اَيْدٍ قِصَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "they have little,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "no, power:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "are niggardly"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSiyru Alhim~api", "text_ar": "قَصِيرُ الهِمَّةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Having little ambition"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (O in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bjl", "text_ar": "بجل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~ahu laqaSiyru AlEilomi", "text_ar": "اـِنَّهُ لَقَصِيرُ العِلْمِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily he has little knowledge"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (M.) ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSiyru Aln~asabi", "text_ar": "قَصِيرُ النَّسَبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Having a short pedigree;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whose father is well known, so that when the son mentions him it is sufficient for him, without his extending his lineage to his grandfather."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) [See also a verse below, in this paragraph.] ―         -b7-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HadiyvN qaSiyrN", "text_ar": "حَدِيثٌ قَصِيرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muqotaSarN", "text_ar": "مُقْتَصَرٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "concise,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "comprehensive, and profitable, story,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "narration."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)       -A2-  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I. q."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maqoSuwrN", "text_ar": "مَقْصُورٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maqoSuwrapN", "text_ar": "مَقْصُورَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Shortened; contracted:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "confined; restricted; limited;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.] ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_imoraA^apN", "text_ar": "اـِمْرَاَةٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSiyru AlxuTaY", "text_ar": "قَصِيرُ الخُطَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlxaTowi", "text_ar": "الخَطْوِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maqoSuwrapu", "text_ar": "مَقْصُورَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A woman whose steps are shortened,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "contracted;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] likened to one who is shackled, whose steps are shortened, or contracted, by the shackles. (Fr.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "farasN", "text_ar": "فَرَسٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSiyrN", "text_ar": "قَصِيرٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A mare that is brought near"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to the tent or dwelling"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and treated generously, and not left to seek for pasture, because she is precious:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a mare that is kept confined."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSiyrapN", "text_ar": "قَصِيرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [which is extr., for by rule it should be without"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSuwrapN", "text_ar": "قَصُورَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Az, S, M, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maqoSuwrapN", "text_ar": "مَقْصُورَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) A woman"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "confined in the house,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "tent, not suffered to go forth:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, K:) a woman"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "kept behind,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "within, the curtain:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA, in explanation of the last of these three epithets:) a girl"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "kept with care, that does not go out:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Az:) the pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qSwrp", "text_ar": "قصورة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSaAy^iru", "text_ar": "قَصَايِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":] [and so, app., of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qSyrp", "text_ar": "قصيرة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":] when you mean short in stature, you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSiyrapN", "text_ar": "قَصِيرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[only], and the pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qiSaArN", "text_ar": "قِصَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) Kutheiyir says"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "waA^anoti Al~atiY Hab~aboti kul~a qaSiyrapK\n                      \n                     \n                        A_ilaY~a wamaA tadoriY bi*aAka AlqaSaAy^iru\n                      \n                     \n                        Eanayotu qaSiyraAti AlHijaAli walamo A^urido\n                      \n                     \n                        qiSaAra AlxuTaY $ar~u Aln~isaA='i AlbaHaAtiru"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M) or, as Fr relates it,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kul~a qaSuwrapF", "text_ar": "كُلَّ قَصُورَةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And thou art the person who hath made every female confined within the house to be an object of love to me, while the females confined within the house know not that: I mean those confined within the curtained canopies: I do not mean the short in step: the worst of women are the short and compressed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. And a poet says"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "waA^ahowaY mina Aln~iswaAni kul~a qaSiyrapK\n                      \n                     \n                        lahaA nasabN fiY AlS~aAliHiyna qaSiyru"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And I love, of women, every one that is confined within the house, that has a short pedigree, among the good"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; i. e., every ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maqoSuwrap", "text_ar": "مَقْصُورَة", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", of whom it suffices to mention her descent from her father, because of his being well known. (M.) Hence, in the Kur, [lv. 72,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HuwrN maqoSuwraAtN fiY", "text_ar": "حُورٌ مَقْصُورَاتٌ فِى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlxiyaAmi", "text_ar": "الخِيَامِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Damsels having eyes whereof the white is intensely white and the black intensely black,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "confined in the pavilions,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Az, Msb,) which are of pearls, for their husbands; (Az;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "concealed by curtains:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Az, Bd:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "confined to their husbands, and not raising their eyes to others:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Fr:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having their eyes restricted to their husbands."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Bd.) And ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naAqapN maqoSuwrapN", "text_ar": "نَاقَةٌ مَقْصُورَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maqoSuwrapN EalaY AlEiyaAli", "text_ar": "مَقْصُورَةٌ عَلَى العِيَالِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A she-camel retained"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "restrictively"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "for the household, that they"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "alone"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "may drink her milk."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, TA. *) ―         -b5-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "quSorapN", "text_ar": "قُصْرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": ["M", "K", "S", "Msb", "Az", "Bd", "Fr", "TA"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}